<TITLE> CU student hacked to death </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Feb 11 (bdnews24.com)A Chittagong University student was hacked to death at a city rail station on Thursday, in the latest of a violent spate of campus-related killings. CU proctor Dr Md Jashimuddin told bdnews24.com the student's body was recovered at around 8:30pm at the port city's Sholoshohor Rail Station. The proctor could not confirm the dead student's identity or whether he had any political affiliation. Both Islami Chhatra Shibir and Bangladesh Chhatra League claimed the dead student as one of their members but were also unable to confirm his name. Nabyajoti Khisha, officer in charge of Pachlaish Police Station, said the student was rescued from the back of tea-stalls beside the rail tracks of the station in a bloody state and rushed to Chittagong Medical College Hospital. A constable of the police camp at CMCH said that doctors declared him dead after his bloodied body was brought in. A university-bound shuttle train makes a stop at Sholoshohor Station at 8:50pm. Police are speculating that the student waiting for the train when he was attacked. bd
